We may refer the adverbial suffixes -θεν, -θι, -θα, -κι to a pronominal origin. To -θεν, as in αἰνόθεν αἰνῶς, and -θι, as in ἠῶθι πρό, we can find no parallel in the cognate languages. With -κι, as¹ in οὐκί, πολλάκι, we can compare A.-S. lit, the neuter of he.
